[18.47, "o", "FOUND  3 findings (2 high, 1 medium)\r\n"]
[18.51, "o", "       source: measured\r\n"]
[18.55, "o", "\r\n"]
[18.59, "o", "  1. [HIGH    ] fitts_undersized_target\r\n"]
[18.63, "o", "     elements: close\r\n"]
[18.67, "o", "     Element 'close' is 32dp on its shorter side, below the minimum tap target (48dp).\r\n"]
[18.71, "o", "     \u2192 Increase the touchable area to at least 48dp, either by growing the element or by extending the hit area (Compose: Modifier.minimumInteractiveComponentSize; SwiftUI: .contentShape; UIKit: hitTest override).\r\n"]
[18.75, "o", "     metric: smaller_side=32.00, minimum=48.00\r\n"]
[18.79, "o", "\r\n"]
[18.83, "o", "  2. [HIGH    ] reach_primary_in_top_corner\r\n"]
[18.87, "o", "     elements: save\r\n"]
[18.91, "o", "     Primary action 'save' is in a top corner (x=374, y=48), the hardest area to reach one-handed on any modern phone size.\r\n"]
[18.95, "o", "     \u2192 Move primary actions into the bottom half of the screen, ideally bottom-centre or within a bottom bar. Top corners are acceptable for low-frequency actions (close, settings, more).\r\n"]
[18.99, "o", "     metric: x=374.00, y=48.00\r\n"]
[19.03, "o", "\r\n"]
[19.07, "o", "  3. [MEDIUM  ] hick_overload\r\n"]
[19.11, "o", "     elements: nav1, nav2, nav3, nav4, nav5, nav6, nav7\r\n"]
[19.15, "o", "     Group 'bottom_nav' has 7 equally-weighted choices. Hick's law: decision time grows logarithmically with choice count, and beyond 5 options users start to slow down or skim past.\r\n"]
[19.19, "o", "     \u2192 Reduce to \u22645, or introduce visual hierarchy (primary action, grouping, progressive disclosure) so the choices stop being weighted equally.\r\n"]
[19.23, "o", "     metric: n=7.00, ceiling=5.00\r\n"]
[19.27, "o", "\r\n"]
